gitCommit.subject: fix(chunking): tighten chunk geometry to surface buried critiques (#304)
gitCommit.body:
fix(chunking): tighten chunk geometry to surface buried critiques (#304)

BEFORE (buried critiques in promotional slabs):
- TARGET_CHARS = 3000
- MIN_CHARS = 800
- CHUNK_MAX_TOKENS = 6000
- CHUNK_HARD_MAX_TOKENS = 8192

AFTER (coherent, retrievable chunks):
- TARGET_CHARS = 1400 (~250-350 tokens)
- MIN_CHARS = 500 (avoid tiny shreds)
- CHUNK_MAX_TOKENS = 450 (hard cap)
- CHUNK_HARD_MAX_TOKENS = 600
- OVERLAP_CHARS = 200 (reduced from 300)

Root cause analysis:
- MNY critique sections ('should not be replicated', 'QOZ mismatch',
  'no tenants', 'Austal relationship') were buried in 3000+ char chunks
  that also contained promotional content
- When scored, positive content dominated, critiques never surfaced
- Smaller chunks ensure each distinct argument can be retrieved independently

IMPORTANT: After this deploys, MNY docs must be re-ingested to get
new chunk boundaries. Existing chunks in Pinecone will still be large.

AI-Tool: Cursor
AI-Model: Claude 4 Opus
AI-Session: docs/ai/sessions/2025-11-27-phase-2-5-adaptive-topk.md
Locks: none (affects future ingestion only)
